Hanley Ramirez|work=The Boston Globe|first=Alex|last=Speier|date=May 25, 2018|accessdate=May 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/RedSox/status/1000037175566766085</ref>\n* June 28: OF/1B [[Steve Pearce (baseball)|Steve Pearce]] was acquired from the [[Toronto Blue Jays]] for minor league infielder [https://www.baseball-reference.com/register/player.fcgi?id=espina000san Santiago Espinal].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/red-sox-acquire-steve-pearce-from-blue-jays/c-283420492 |title=Red Sox acquire OF Pearce from Blue Jays |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=June 28, 2018 |accessdate=June 28, 2018}}</ref>\n* July 25: Pitcher [[Jalen Beeks]] was traded to the [[Tampa Bay Rays]] for pitcher [[Nathan Eovaldi]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/boston-red-sox/2018/07/25/red-sox-rays-nathan-eovaldi-trade |title=Red Sox acquire Nathan Eovaldi from Rays |first=Andrew |last=Mahoney |website=[[Boston.com]] |date=July 25, 2018 |accessdate=July 25, 2018}}</ref>\n* July 30: Second baseman [[Ian Kinsler]] was acquired from the [[Los Angeles Angels]] for Triple-A pitchers [[Ty Buttrey]] and [[Williams Jerez]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/ian-kinsler-traded-to-red-sox/c-288130632 |title=With Pedroia's return uncertain, Sox get Kinsler |first=Ian |last=Browne |website=[[MLB.com]] |date=July 31, 2018 |accessdate=July 31, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Amateur draft===\nBoston's first 15 selections in the [[2018 Major League Baseball draft|2018 MLB draft]], held on June 4\u20136, are listed below.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://boston.redsox.mlb.com/team/draft.jsp?c_id=bos&year=2018 |title=Boston Red Sox 2018 Draft Selections |website=[[MLB.com]] |accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Round\n! scope=\"col\"| Pick\n! scope=\"col\"| Player\n! scope=\"col\"| Position\n! scope=\"col\"| B/T\n! scope=\"col\"| Class\n! scope=\"col\"| School\n! scope=\"col\"| Sign date\n|-\n|1\n